TY  - JOUR
TI  - Quasi-Equilibria in Markets with Non-Convex Preferences
AU  - Starr, Ross M.
AB  - [A pure exchange economy is considered without the assumption of convex preferences. It is shown that the divergence from equilibrium due to non-convexity is bounded in a fashion independent of the number of traders. For a sufficiently large number of traders there are configurations arbitrarily close to equilibrium.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1969
DB  - JSTOR
